00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:46,146
Here they come!

266
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:49,816
Hurry this up.
I want a war.

267
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:50,942
Hey, Fern.

268
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,318
[Whoosh]

269
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:53,778
Uncle Gumbald!

270
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:56,823
I demand that you de-escalate
your forces now.

271
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:59,075
[Chuckles]
Listen to yourself.

272
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,785
You're a toddler, Bonnibel.

273
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:02,954
[Gasps]
Surrender or die!

274
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:04,956
- Nol!
- That's my cue!

275
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,333
- What?
- Hyap-pow!

276
00:11:11,588 --> 00:11:14,716
[Screaming]

277
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:17,802
They're dead!
They're actually dead!

278
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:21,347
BMO:
And so they were dead.

279
00:11:25,977 --> 00:11:27,729
No. Not dead.

280
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:31,107
What is this place?

281
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,066
Finn?!

282
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,610
Last resort!

283
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:36,571
Sorry, Pb, but you were acting
like total nuts out there.

284
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:40,200
Now you guys have to hash this
out in the unconscious world.

285
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:42,869
This is a dream?

286
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:44,078
Yeah, man.

287
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,748
You can basically do anything
in dreams.

288
00:11:46,873 --> 00:11:48,249
[Ding!]

289
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,626
[Munch!]

290
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,504
Sneak attack!

291
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:56,341
If we destroy them here,

292
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,593
maybe they'll die
in the real world.

293
00:11:58,635 --> 00:11:59,719
BUBBLEGUM: Psh!

294
00:11:59,761 --> 00:12:01,763
Not if I destroy you first!

295
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:04,265
No! We need love, not war!

296
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,767
- Good idea.
-[Ding!]

297
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:07,143
Love bazooka!

298
00:12:07,227 --> 00:12:10,647
Put down your weapons,
or I'll bazooka you!

299
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:12,523
- UNCLE GUMBALD: No!
-[Clanking]

300
00:12:12,649 --> 00:12:16,736
POODLE:
[Vocalizing]

301
00:12:16,778 --> 00:12:21,658
J Dreamin' of imagination &

302
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:26,412
J Give me imagination J

303
00:12:26,496 --> 00:12:29,249
s So I can dream of a kiss J

304
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:29,999
J My dream...

305
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,126
Thank goodness
for a singing pot beast

306
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,795
to de-escalate the situation.

307
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:36,130
J Imaginary way J

308
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:37,173
[Whoosh!]

309
00:12:37,924 --> 00:12:39,300
J Dream J
- Oh!

310
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:43,263
[Poodle scatting in distance]

311
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:48,268
Oh, this sandwich
is way too much for me.

312
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:50,895
Jermaine always liked
splitting sandwiches.

313
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,439
Mmm!

314
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:54,691
Thanks, bro.

315
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:58,695
I'm gonna figure out
how to wake myself up

316
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:02,031
and take my revenge
on you sleeping chumps!

317
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:03,533
You're leaving me?

318
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:05,827
You're on your own, kid.

319
00:13:05,827 --> 00:13:06,536
[Whoosh!]

320
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:11,958
He's rooting into the ground.

321
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,960
Ready, aim.

322
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,545
No!

323
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:20,591
You're supposed to be
having some kind of epiphany.

324
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:21,801
[Whoosh!]

325
00:13:21,843 --> 00:13:24,971
Here's my epiphany.
You've gone rogue on me!

326
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:27,724
I'm outtie five thou!

327
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:31,561
Fern! [Grunts]

328
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,062
Come on!
Snap out of it, man!

329
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:35,606
Aaaah!

330
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,233
I don't need your help.

331
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,113
Jake, help me!

332
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,991
I want to help you,
but I can't lose this job.

333
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:45,992
[Fingers snapping]

334
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:48,578
Waiter, oh, waiter.

335
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:49,996
Dude.

336
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:53,374
[Screeching]

337
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:57,754
I'm going to fly around
and wreck things

338
00:13:57,754 --> 00:14:01,758
until I feel better
or until I tire myself out.

339
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,593
Peaceful thoughts.

340
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:05,261
[Poink!]

341
00:14:05,345 --> 00:14:06,763
[Screeching]

342
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:08,097
FINN: Fern!

343
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:10,099
It all looks so good.

344
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:11,893
[Fern screeching]

345
00:14:11,893 --> 00:14:13,519
What's up with that bird?

346
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:15,646
Why are you looking at me, bird?

347
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:16,898
[Both scream]

348
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:18,524
Bad bird!

349
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:23,029
[Sighs]

350
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:25,907
Everybody gets
an evil doppelganger but me.

351
00:14:25,907 --> 00:14:28,618
I'll be your evil doppelganger.

352
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:30,536
Jermaine, you're the best!

353
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,288
[Both laughing]

354
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:36,918
[Both laughing]

355
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:38,669
Enough, Gumbald!

356
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:40,922
[Both grunt]

357
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:45,385
Pinch me.
I want to wake up!

358
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,677
BUBBLEGUM:
Gumbald!

359
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:49,013
We're ending this here.

360
00:14:49,055 --> 00:14:50,932
So be it.

361
00:14:53,643 --> 00:14:55,395
[Poink! Poink!]

362
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:02,568
[High-pitched whirring]

363
00:15:02,652 --> 00:15:03,277
[Screeching]

364
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:05,071
FINN: If you could just
calm down and be cool,

365
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:07,198
it would be a great thing
that there's two of us.

366
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:09,951
[Screeching, screams]

367
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,079
Aah!

368
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:17,583
Why don't you just fight me
like a real butterfly!

369
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,585
We're two sides
of the same coin.

370
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:22,422
You'll never understand
what it's like to be me.

371
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,549
I'm tormented!

372
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,051
I'm also that sometimes!

373
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:29,804
Prove it.
Or I'll never stop fighting you.

374
00:15:29,846 --> 00:15:31,472
[Both laughing]

375
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,725
Oh, geez,
how's he gonna do that?

376
00:15:34,809 --> 00:15:35,560
Hmm?

377
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,729
Finn, we'll be right back.

378
00:15:38,813 --> 00:15:40,106
FINN:
Okay. Aah!

379
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:41,858
[Both laughing]

380
00:15:47,864 --> 00:15:49,615
Come on, Little Gum.

381
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:51,993
Don't run away from happiness.

382
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:53,369
I'm gonna fix you.

383
00:15:53,453 --> 00:15:54,954
No, no, no!

384
00:15:54,996 --> 00:15:57,498
Just one drop.

385
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:58,624
Drip a drop.

386
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,251
I drip a drop.

387
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:03,880
Not gonna stop
till I drip a drop.

388
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,506
Hmm?

389
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:06,340
[Pop!]

390
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:07,884
[Bubblegum laughs]

391
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:09,719
Drip, drip!

392
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,387
[Gasps]

393
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,598
The juice!

394
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,641
No!

395
00:16:17,018 --> 00:16:19,145
[Giggles] What-what!

396
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,524
Call me...Princess.

397
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:31,365
JERMAINE:
What are we looking for?

398
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:32,992
I can't quite picture it.

399
00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:35,661
But I'm pretty sure
Finn buried it here.

400
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:38,289
JERMAINE:
In the underground balloon mall.

401
00:16:39,624 --> 00:16:41,250
Remember how much
balloon animals

402
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:42,752
used to cheer Finn up?

403
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,545
- Yeah.
-[Speaks Korean]

404
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,421
Huh?

405
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:49,759
Uh...Lady, where's Jermaine?

406
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:50,885
Shh.

407
00:16:52,386 --> 00:16:53,763
[Speaking Korean]

408
00:16:58,893 --> 00:16:59,810
JAKE: Aww.

409
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:01,771
Sleepy puppies.

410
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:03,773
Yee!

411
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,026
[All hiss]

412
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,486
And I'm done!

413
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:10,279
[Speaking Korean]

414
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:11,531
What? Oof!

415
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:12,907
[Gasps]

416
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:17,995
Your farts aren't funny, Dad!

417
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:20,540
Noooooo!

418
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,291
[Sobbing]

419
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:24,794
[Sniffing]

420
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:29,298
[Sniffing continues]

421
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,177
Huh?

422
00:17:33,261 --> 00:17:34,679
Oh, dang!

423
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:36,806
Is that Finn's vault?

424
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:37,807
[Farting]

425
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,309
Aaaggh!
Nightmare fart!

426
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:53,698
BUBBLEGUM:
It's beautiful.

427
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:02,164
[Rumbling]

428
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:03,833
[All screaming]

429
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:07,336
No!

430
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:11,090
Oh, why didn't T build
an armature?

431
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:12,717
[Grunts]

432
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,343
I can help you, Princess.

433
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:16,846
Just listen to this.

434
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:20,182
Watch me do my Tiny Taffy dance!

435
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:22,685
[Vocalizing]

436
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:28,190
[Laughs]

437
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:30,943
[Sobbing]

438
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:33,362
[Growling]

439
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:37,116
Fern, come on!
I'm not fighting you.

440
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,994
-[Growls]
-[Grunts]

441
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,120
[Both sniffing]

442
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,873
BOTH:
Oh, what reeks?

443
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:46,125
Repressed memories!

444
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:48,502
My vault!?
My vault!?

445
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:49,712
Proof!

446
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:51,964
-[Whirring]
-[Both scream]

447
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:56,510
See, this is our shared torment!

448
00:18:56,636 --> 00:18:57,887
[Both screaming]

449
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,973
Dude, I blocked this stuff out
for a reason!

450
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:02,767
Well, now you know how I feel

451
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,226
about knowing how you feel
about --

452
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:06,979
Okay, okay!
Just make it stop!

453
00:19:07,021 --> 00:19:09,482
We gotta confront them head-on!

454
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,033
[Both gasp]

455
00:19:19,659 --> 00:19:20,618
Fern.

456
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,912
This is why I brought us here.

457
00:19:23,037 --> 00:19:24,914
We can defeat him together.

458
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:34,799
BUBBLEGUM: No fear.

459
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:42,181
[Grunts]

460
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,766
[Snhap!]

461
00:19:43,808 --> 00:19:45,810
So you're the nasty grass wad

462
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,937
that's been holding
my Finn boy hostage.

463
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,189
Without me, he's got no body.

464
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:51,691
So back off.

465
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:53,693
You sicken me.

466
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:56,070
[Screeches]

467
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:00,032
[Whooshing]

468
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:05,579
[Vocalizing]

469
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,293
I'm me again.

470
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:13,963
It feels like it's been years.

471
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:17,299
[Belches]

472
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:23,681
[Gasps]

473
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:26,851
He was right.
I've got no body.

474
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,853
Ah, don't worry.

475
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:30,604
It's just a dream!

476
00:20:31,689 --> 00:20:34,859
[Screaming]

477
00:20:34,859 --> 00:20:37,987
They're dead!
They're actually dead!

478
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:40,990
Never mind!
They're okay!

479
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:43,075
Fern!

480
00:20:43,117 --> 00:20:45,244
You really are disintegrating!

481
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,829
My bad.

482
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:51,333
Bonnie, I --

483
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:53,377
I'm so sorry for
what I put you through

484
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:55,004
for all those centuries.

485
00:20:55,129 --> 00:20:57,006
The Candy Kingdom
was your dream,

486
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:58,632
and I took it from you.

487
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:00,968
Bonnie, that means
so much to me.

488
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,971
Come. From now on,
we'll live in peace.

489
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:05,890
Oop! Whoaal

490
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:06,974
[Glass shatters]

491
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,769
Drat.

492
00:21:09,852 --> 00:21:10,853
What?!

493
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:12,772
[Whoosh!]

494
00:21:12,855 --> 00:21:15,274
[Laughing]
Woo-hoo-hoo!

495
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:18,402
He never was the epiphany type.

496
00:21:18,486 --> 00:21:21,864
But I am willing to let
bygones be bygones.

497
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:23,866
Very well.

498
00:21:23,908 --> 00:21:27,161
Two Candy Kingdoms it is!

499
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:29,288
ALL: Hurray!

500
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,290
BMO:
And so, in the end,

501
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:34,126
they decided not to have
the big fight.

502
00:21:34,168 --> 00:21:37,379
Oh! So, you meant,
like, the end of the war.

503
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:39,381
I thought you meant, like,
the end of the world.

504
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:41,133
No, no, no.

505
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,385
That happened next.

506
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:46,555
So I guess everyone's
just going home, huh?

507
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,057
Yep.

508
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,810
[Humming, whirring]

509
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:56,065
We donked up for real.

510
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,567
[Humming, whirring]

511
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:06,826
Jake...what am I lookin' at?

512
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:08,410
Uh...

513
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:10,287
we saved the day.

514
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:12,414
So, maybe that big baby's here

515
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:14,959
to give us presents
for doing a good job.

516
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:16,794
[Wind gusting]

517
00:22:16,836 --> 00:22:20,339
Okay, I'm not an expert,
but this seems bad.

518
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:22,091
You ain't kiddin', shrubs.

519
00:22:23,551 --> 00:22:25,803
Oh, no.

520
00:22:25,845 --> 00:22:26,846
[Camera shutter clicks]

521
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:30,224
Bonniel

522
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:32,351
What did you do?!

523
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:33,602
It wasn't me!

524
00:22:35,229 --> 00:22:38,482
It's been real cool being in
this rogue's gallery with you.

525
00:22:38,566 --> 00:22:40,609
Me and Gunther
were gonna go, uh --

526
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:44,446
Oh...
my...

527
00:22:44,488 --> 00:22:45,865
SIMON: Golb!

528
00:22:45,990 --> 00:22:47,199
Look, Betty.

529
00:22:47,241 --> 00:22:48,617
I keep seeing reference

530
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:51,704
to this mysterious entity
that embodies chaos.

531
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:54,456
That's great!
Come on, let's make sundaes.

532
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:56,959
Golb would say ice cream
is without meaning.

533
00:22:57,001 --> 00:23:00,004
Just empty calories
devoid of purpose.

534
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:02,381
Good thing he isn't here, then.

535
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:07,386
His presence is felt in every
crevice where chaos lurks.

536
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:11,891
Imagine if we could somehow
harness all that dank energy.

537
00:23:11,891 --> 00:23:12,892
BETTY: Hey!

538
00:23:12,892 --> 00:23:15,394
You want some cherries
with that chocolate syrup?

539
